UT Bank of Ghana Rises to 2 1/2-Month High on Dividend Plan

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-03-16T16:19:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/ut-bank-of-ghana-rises-to-2-1-2-month-high-on-dividend-plan.html
  UT Bank Ltd. (UTB) , a Ghanaian lender,
rose to the highest in 2 1/2-months as investors bought shares
in anticipation of a dividend payment.  The stock gained 2 pesewas, or 7.4 percent, to close at 29
pesewas, by 3 p.m. in Accra, the highest since Dec. 31.  “Investors want to take part in a dividend payment by the
bank on April 29 in respect of the 2010 financial year,”
Enyonam Dagadu, head of stock brokerage at African Alliance said
by phone from Accra. “The bank will pay 1 pesewa per share as
dividend.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 